  },
  {
    "id": "sample2-q002",
    "type": "mcq",
    "topic": "cloud-computing",
    "subtopic": "serverless",
    "stem": "Serverless computing allows users to:",
    "options": [
      {
        "label": "A",
        "text": "Manage physical servers",
        "isCorrect": false
      },
      {
        "label": "B",
        "text": "Run code without managing servers",
        "isCorrect": true
      },
      {
        "label": "C",
        "text": "Store unlimited data",
        "isCorrect": false
      },
      {
        "label": "D",
        "text": "Build hardware",
        "isCorrect": false
      }
    ],
    "answerOptionLabels": [
      "B"
    ],
    "source": {
      "file": "Sample -2.pdf",
      "exam": "bank",
      "tier": "practice",
      "originalNumber": 2
    },
    "keyProvenance": "answer_page",
    "flags": [],
    "keyVerified": true,
    "needsReview": false,
    "dedupeHash": "8f2268bfbd4c181f537024312c71317a8485b47f",
    "explanation": "Serverless (FaaS) means the provider owns provisioning, scaling and patching of the servers; the customer only uploads code that runs on an event. Servers still exist, they are just invisible to the user, so A is the inverse of the model."
  },
  {
    "id": "sample2-q003",
    "type": "mcq",
    "topic": "cloud-computing",
    "subtopic": "serverless",
    "stem": "AWS Lambda is an example of:",
    "options": [
      {
        "label": "A",
